{"title_page": "Rudraveena (teleserial)", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{copyedit |date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Rudraveenai\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Mystery film|mystery]]-[[Thriller film|suspense]]\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = Rudhraveenai novel by [[Indra Soundar Rajan]]\n| writer                   = [[Indra Soundar Rajan]]\n| director                 = Rakesh Sinha\n| starring                 = [[Chetan (actor)| Chethan]] <br> [[Santhoshi]] <br> [[Kaveri (Tamil actress) | Kaveri]] <br> [[Bala Singh]] <br> [[Y. G. Mahendra]]\n| country                  = [[Tamil Nadu]]\n| language                 = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| num_episodes             = 106\n| list_episodes            = \n| producer                 = [[Radhika]]\n| company                  = [[Radaan Mediaworks]] \nEnterprises\n| theme_music_composer     = Ramesh Krishna\n| opentheme                = \n| location                 = [[Tamil Nadu]]\n| cinematography           = \n| editing                  = \n| camera                   = [[Multi-camera]]\n| runtime                  = Approx. 20-22 minutes per \nepisode\n| channel                  = [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]]\n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| status                   = \n| preceded_by              = Pudhayal Bhoomi @ 8:30PM (Wednesday)\n| followed_by              = [[Chidambara Rahasiyam (TV series)| Chidhambara Ragasiyam]] @ 8.30PM (Wednesday)\n| related                  = \n| production_website       = \n| image_alt                = \n| num_seasons              = 1\n| network                  = Sun TV\n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n}}\n'''''Rudraveena''''' is a Tamil [[Mystery film|mystery]]-[[Thriller film|suspense]] television series and an adaptation of [[Indra Soundar Rajan]]'s book bearing the same name. It was directed by Rakesh Sinha. From 2002 to 2004, the series was broadcasted through 106 episodes on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]] on Wednesdays at 8:30 p.m.  In this time-slot, Rudraveena replaced another [[Mystery film|mystery]]-[[Thriller film|suspense]] series called ''Pudhayal Bhoomi''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rangarajan|first=Malathi|title=  Fascination for the mysterious  |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2009/01/16/stories/2009011650520400.htm|accessdate=20 August 2010|date=16 January 2009|location=Chennai, India|work=The Hindu}}</ref> This series was remade in [[Malayalam]] bearing the same name, but with significant changes to the story. However, the past segment with Baba was dubbed from the Tamil version.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Chetan (actor)| Chethan]] as Swaminathan (Kalyana Sundaram's son, Mythili's love interest)[AD 2003]\n*[[Y. G. Mahendra]] as \"Sakthi Upasagar\" Narasima Barathi [AD 2003]\n*Nisha / ''replaced by'' Vanaja as Mythili (Pattar's mute elder daughter)[AD 2003]\n*Sreeram as Sankaran (Pattar's only son, Banu's lover)[AD 2003]\n*Megha as Banu, Dasi Sundramba's daughter (Shankaran's lover, Swaminathan's one-sided love interest)[AD 2003]\n*Shylaja as Dasi Sundaramba (Banu's mother)[AD 2003]\n*[[Aadukalam Naren]] as Ramachandran, Sundaramba's husband[AD 2003]\n*S Gnanavel as Baba(AD 1702)\n*[[Santhoshi]] as Dasi Abaraajitha Vaijayanthi(AD 1702) [Banu, Sundaramba, Manicavalli's ancestor]\n*[[Kaveri (Tamil actress) | Kaveri]] as Dasi Malli  (Abaraajitha Vaijayanthi's mother)(AD 1702)\n*Charukesh as Veerendra (Aparaajitha Vaijayanthi's brother)(AD 1702) / Ashokan (Banu's half-brother)/(Baba) [AD 2003]\n*[[Bala Singh]] as Kalyanasundaram (Village President and Swaminathan's father)[AD 2003]\n*Gauthami Vembunathan as Rangayi (Kalyanasundam\u2019s wife and Swaminathan\u2019s mother)[AD 2003]\n*Vijay Anand as Ganesan, Karnam's son (Gayathri's lover)[AD 2003]\n  -- as Karnam[AD 2003]\n  -- as Annapoorani, Karnam's wife[AD 2003]\n*Uma Maheshwari as Akhila (Ganesan\u2019s cousin who wants to marry him)[AD 2003]\n*Sreenivasan as Vaithilingam (Kovil Pattar, Shankaran, Mythili and Gayathri's father)[AD 2003]\n*Archana as Gayathri (Ganesan's lover)[AD 2003] and as Neelakandan (Guruji's spy)[AD 2003]\n*Nagalakshmi as Thilagam (Dasi family's helper)[AD 2003]\n*Rani Somanathan as Dasi Manicavalli (Dasi Sundramaba's mother and Banu\u2019s Grandmother)[AD 2003] and as Sastrigal(AD 1702)[Karnam's ancestor]\n*Banu Prakash as Rudheashwar (Reincarnation of Kabaligan)[AD 2003]\n*Deepa as Manthrini, Rudheashwar's assistant [AD 2003]\n*Ramachandran as Kabaligan(AD 1702)and as Vettiyaan Karuppan[AD 2003]\n\n==Plot==\nRudhra Veenai is a mystery thriller revolving around the Hindu musical instrument Veena. The Veenai is made by Lord Shiva himself. The Veenai is also Lord Parvati in instrumental form. Miracles would occur when certain tunes were played on it. The Rudhra Veenai arrives in Thodipuram carried by a Muslim man called Nawab Jan Baba, in AD 1702. 300 years later, in the year 2002, Thodipuram becomes the most prosperous village in South India because it housed the Rudhra Veenai. Mysterious happenings occur at Rani Bungalow, where Baba's spirit is believed to be roaming. Only women from the Dasi family could enter and leave the Bungalow without harm. Many people claiming to be Rudhran try to attain the Rudhra Veenai. The claims to be Rudhran are grounded in the logic that only a Rudhran sent by Lord Shiva would be able to play the Rudhra Veena.\n\nWho is the Rudhran? Where does the Veena go? Who plays the Veena every night? What is causing the heavy protection around the Rani Bungalow? Why are the Dasi women going to the Bungalow at night and engaging in some mysterious Poojai? All these questions are answered as the show progresses.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n==External links==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLormYfA9XqyDlyMCKj0ag1vr5oEpAXtbt Rudraveenai on Youtube]\n{{Sun TV shows}}\n[