(Wednesday)\n| related                  = \n| production_website       = \n| image_alt                = \n| num_seasons              = 1\n| network                  = Sun TV\n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n}}\n'''''Rudraveena''''' is a Tamil language, [[Mystery film|mystery]]-[[Thriller film|suspense]] television series and adaptation of [[Indra Soundar Rajan]]'s book of the same name; it was directed by Rakesh Sinha. From 2002 to 2004, the series was broadcast on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]] on Wednesdays at 8:30 PM for 106 episodes.  In this time-slot, Rudraveena replaced another [[Mystery film|mystery]]-[[Thriller film|suspense]] series called ''Pudhayal Bhoomi''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rangarajan|first=Malathi|title=  Fascination for the mysterious  |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2009/01/16/stories/2009011650520400.htm|accessdate=20 August 2010|date=16 January 2009|location=Chennai, India|work=The Hindu}}</ref> This series was remade in [[Malayalam]] with the same name, but with significant changes to the story. However, the past segment with Baba was dubbed from the Tamil version.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Chetan (actor)| Chethan]] as Swaminathan (Kalyana Sundaram's son, Mythili's love interest)[AD 2003]\n*[[Y. G. Mahendra]] as \"Sakthi Upasagar\" Narasima Barathi [AD 2003]\n*Nisha / ''replaced by'' Vanaja as Mythili (Pattar's mute elder daughter)[AD 2003]\n*Sreeram as Sankaran (Pattar's only son, Banu's lover)[AD 2003]\n*Megha as Banu, Dasi Sundramba's daughter (Shankaran's lover, Swaminathan's one-sided love interest)[AD 2003]\n*Shylaja as Dasi Sundaramba (Banu's mother)[AD 2003]\n*[[Aadukalam Naren]] as Ramachandran, Sundaramba's husband[AD 2003]\n*S Gnanavel as Baba(AD 1702)\n*[[Santhoshi]] as Dasi Abaraajitha Vaijayanthi(AD 1702) [Banu, Sundaramba, Manicavalli's ancestor]\n*[[Kaveri (Tamil actress) | Kaveri]] as Dasi Malli  (Abaraajitha Vaijayanthi's mother)(AD 1702)\n*Charukesh as Veerendra (Aparaajitha Vaijayanthi's brother)(AD 1702) / Ashokan (Banu's half-brother)/(Baba) [AD 2003]\n*[[Bala Singh]] as Kalyanasundaram (Village President and Swaminathan's father)[AD 2003]\n*Gauthami Vembunathan as Rangayi (Kalyanasundam\u2019s wife and Swaminathan\u2019s mother)[AD 2003]\n*Vijay Anand as Ganesan, Karnam's son (Gayathri's lover)[AD 2003]\n  -- as Karnam[AD 2003]\n  -- as Annapoorani, Karnam's wife[AD 2003]\n*Uma Maheshwari as Akhila (Ganesan\u2019s cousin who wants to marry him)[AD 2003]\n*Sreenivasan as Vaithilingam (Kovil Pattar, Shankaran, Mythili and Gayathri's father)[AD 2003]\n*Archana as Gayathri (Ganesan's lover)[AD 2003] and as Neelakandan (Guruji's spy)[AD 2003]\n*Nagalakshmi as Thilagam (Dasi family's helper)[AD 2003]\n*Rani Somanathan as Dasi Manicavalli (Dasi Sundramaba's mother and Banu\u2019s Grandmother)[AD 2003] and as Sastrigal(AD 1702)[Karnam's ancestor]\n*Banu Prakash as Rudheashwar (Reincarnation of Kabaligan)[AD 2003]\n*Deepa as Manthrini, Rudheashwar's assistant [AD 2003]\n*Ramachandran as Kabaligan(AD 1702)and as Vettiyaan Karuppan[AD 2003]\n\n==Plot==\nRudhra Veenai is a mystery thriller revolving around the Hindu musical instrument of the same name. The Veenai is made by Lord Shiva himself. The Veenai is also Lord Parvati in instrumental form. Many miracles would occur when certain tunes were played on it. Rudhra Veenai arrives in Thodipuram carried by a Muslim man called Nawab Jan Baba, in AD 1702. 300 years later, in the year 2002, Thodipuram became the most prosperous village in South India, all because of the Rudhra Veenai. Mysterious happenings occur at Rani Bungalow, where it is believed Baba's spirit is roaming. Yet, only women from the Dasi Family could enter and leave the Bungalow without harm. Many people claiming to be Rudhran, try to attain the Rudhra Veenai. The claims to be Rudhran are grounded in the logic that only a Rudhran sent by Lord Shiva would be able to play the Rudhra Veena.\n\nWho is the Rudhran? Where does the Veena go? Who plays the Veena every night? What is causing the heavy protection around the Rani Bungalow? Why are the Dasi women going to the Bungalow at night and engaging in some mysterious Poojai? All these questions are answered as the show progresses.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n==External links==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLormYfA9XqyDlyMCKj0ag1vr5oEpAXtbt Rudraveenai on Youtube]\n{{Sun TV shows}}\n[[Category:Sun TV television series]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu drama television series]]\n[[Category:2002 Tamil-language television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2004 Tamil-language television series endings]]\n[[Category:2000s Tamil-language television series]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television programmes based on Indian novels]]\n", "name_user": "Meldondsouza", "label": "safe", "comment": "Regular grammatical errors were edited.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rudraveena_(teleserial)"}
